    "contentMarkdown": "Agentic commerce — AI agents that shop, compare, and sometimes check out for humans — stopped being a thought experiment in 2026 and started showing up in retailer analytics dashboards.\n\n## Adoption is real, but checkout trust lags discovery\n\nSurveys show **73% of consumers** now use AI somewhere in their shopping journey — 45% for product ideas, 37% for summarizing reviews, 32% for comparing prices. But the funnel narrows sharply at the final step: only **13% of consumers** have actually completed a purchase referred by an AI assistant. Trust is building quickly, though — **70%** say they're at least somewhat comfortable with an agent completing a purchase for them, and in the US the share of shoppers willing to hand over the entire checkout jumped from **12% to 35%** in about a year.\n\n## The traffic numbers are the clearest signal\n\nRetailer-side data is where the shift is most measurable. AI-referred traffic to US retailers grew **393% year-over-year** in Q1 2026. Shopify — one of the few platforms publishing hard numbers — reported AI-driven traffic to its merchant stores grew **8x year-over-year** in the same quarter, with orders originating from AI-powered searches up nearly **13x**. During holiday-season testing, AI assistant referral traffic converted **700% better than social media** and **200% better than traditional search**.\n\n## Where this is headed\n\nMorgan Stanley expects nearly half of online shoppers to use AI shopping agents by 2030, driving roughly a quarter of their spend. McKinsey pegs the total agentic commerce opportunity at **$3-5 trillion globally by 2030**. For payments and fintech players, the open question is infrastructure: agent-initiated transactions need new authentication, liability, and dispute frameworks that today's card-not-present rules weren't built for — a gap protocol efforts like Stripe's and OpenAI's agentic checkout standards are racing to fill.\n\n## Sources\n\n[Agentic Commerce Stats 2026: Enterprise Guide, commercetools](https://commercetools.com/blog/agentic-commerce-stats-enterprise-guide), [State of AI in E-Commerce 2026, Stord](https://www.stord.com/reports/state-of-ai-2026), [Agentic Commerce Trends and Statistics for 2026, MetaRouter](https://www.metarouter.io/post/agentic-commerce-trends-statistics)."
