    "contentMarkdown": "Cross-border money transfers remain one of the clearest cases where the \"cheap\" option and the advertised option are two different things. Comparing Wise against a traditional bank wire shows just how large that gap still is in 2026.\n\n## Fee structure\n\n**Wise** charges approximately 0.5% of the transfer amount plus a small fixed fee, and applies the real mid-market exchange rate with no hidden markup. **Bank wires** typically charge a flat fee of $30-45, and separately mark up the exchange rate by an estimated 2-4% above mid-market — a cost that's easy to miss because it isn't itemized as a \"fee.\"\n\n## Real numbers\n\nOn a $1,000 transfer to India, one comparison found Wise cost around **$8.20**, versus **$90-105** through Chase. On a $5,000 wire, totals at Chase or Wells Fargo commonly land in the **$200-300** range, while specialist apps like Wise stayed **under $35** for the same transfer. Aggregated across providers, industry trackers estimate savings of **$67-103 per $1,000 sent**, an 85-93% reduction versus a typical big-bank wire.\n\n## Why the exchange rate matters more than the fee\n\nThe flat wire fee is the visible cost, but the exchange-rate markup is usually the bigger one. Banks often mark up rates without clearly disclosing the spread, while Wise and similar specialists use the 0%-markup mid-market rate and charge only a transparent, visible percentage on top.\n\n## Which one wins for which use case\n\nFor personal remittances, freelancer payouts, and most SME cross-border payments, a specialist like Wise is very likely to be meaningfully cheaper and faster. Traditional bank wires still make sense for large, one-off institutional transfers where an existing banking relationship, same-bank settlement, or specific compliance requirements matter more than shaving off transfer cost.\n\n## Sources\n\n[MoneyTransferReviews: Wise vs Bank Wire 2026](https://moneytransferreviews.com/compare/wise-vs-bank-wire), [TransferFees.io: Wire Transfer Fee Calculator 2026](https://transferfees.io/wire-transfer-fee-calculator/), [SendMoneyCompare: Bank Wire Transfer Fees 2026](https://sendmoneycompare.com/guides/bank-wire-transfer-fees-2026)."
