    "contentMarkdown": "For most of 2025, ChatGPT held a commanding majority of the AI-assistant market. That changed in 2026, with rivals eating into its lead even as ChatGPT's own user base kept growing in absolute terms.\n\n## Market share shift\n\nChatGPT's share of the global AI-assistant market dropped from over 50% as recently as January 2026 to **46.4% by the end of May** — the first time it has fallen below half the market. In the same period, **Google's Gemini reached 27.7%**, and **Anthropic's Claude climbed to 10.3%**. Measured differently, by worldwide web-visit share, ChatGPT still leads clearly at **53.9%**, ahead of Gemini's **27.9%** and Claude's **9.2%** — a reminder that \"market share\" varies a lot by methodology.\n\n## Absolute user counts\n\nBy monthly active users, ChatGPT remains far ahead: **over 1.1 billion** monthly users, versus **662 million** for Gemini and **245 million** for Claude.\n\n## Regional patterns\n\nIn the **US**, ChatGPT holds 58.3% web-visit share, Gemini 19.3%, and Claude 13.4%. In **India**, ChatGPT counts roughly 330 million monthly users, Gemini 229 million, and Claude 72.3 million — showing Google's home-market and Android-bundling advantage narrows the gap outside the US.\n\n## The Claude growth story\n\nThe standout trend is Claude's trajectory: its global audience grew **452% year-on-year in May 2026**, and its US audience share climbed from **4.4% to nearly 14%** over twelve months — rising from about 60.2 million monthly users in December 2025 to 245 million by May 2026, roughly a fourfold increase.\n\n## Which one wins for which use case\n\nBy sheer reach, ChatGPT remains the default consumer assistant. Gemini's strength comes from deep integration across Google's Android and Workspace ecosystem. Claude's fastest-growing usage suggests increasing traction among users prioritizing it for coding, writing, and enterprise workflows — a share gain worth watching through the rest of 2026.\n\n## Sources\n\n[TechCrunch: ChatGPT's market share slips below 50%](https://techcrunch.com/2026/06/16/chatgpts-market-share-slips-below-50-for-first-time/), [Business Standard: ChatGPT market share slips below 50%](https://www.business-standard.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/chatgpt-market-share-slips-below-50-google-gemini-anthropic-claude-gain-ground-126061700765_1.html), [MediaNama: ChatGPT's AI market share drops below 50%](https://www.medianama.com/2026/06/223-chatgpts-ai-market-share-drops-below-50-gemini-claude-gain-users-report/)."
