    "contentMarkdown": "Open banking APIs are the plumbing behind most modern fintech apps, and the choice between Plaid and Finicity still comes down to a familiar split: breadth versus lending-specific depth.\n\n## Coverage\n\n**Plaid** connects across **59 countries**, giving it 57 more markets than Finicity, which currently covers just **2 countries**. For any product with international ambitions, Plaid is the clear starting point on reach alone.\n\n## Where each one specializes\n\nThe two platforms diverge sharply by use case. **Plaid** performs best for personal finance apps, investment dashboards, and products needing real-time transaction data and spending categorization. **Finicity** shines specifically in **lending** — mortgage workflows, and VOI/VOA (verification of income/assets) reports — backed by **Mastercard's direct bank relationships** since Mastercard acquired Finicity in 2020.\n\n## Accuracy and reliability\n\nPlaid is typically rated more accurate for transaction categorization, spending insights, and liabilities data. Finicity, meanwhile, offers highly reliable income and asset verification thanks to its deep banking partnerships. On infrastructure, Plaid's move to a distributed architecture in early 2025 measurably improved real-time pull speed, giving it an edge on overall reliability and fewer retries heading into 2026.\n\n## A new cost variable\n\nAn important 2025-2026 development for both platforms: in **June 2025**, JPMorgan Chase told data aggregators it would begin charging for consumer account data access, and by November had updated contracts with Plaid and other major aggregators covering more than 95% of its open banking data requests. This is reshaping unit economics industry-wide, not just for Plaid or Finicity specifically.\n\n## Which one wins for which use case\n\nBuilding a budgeting app, investment tracker, or anything needing broad geographic reach: **Plaid** is the default starting point. Building a mortgage, lending, or income-verification product where bank-grade accuracy on financial data matters most: **Finicity's** Mastercard backing is the stronger fit.\n\n## Sources\n\n[OpenBankingTracker: Finicity vs Plaid 2026](https://www.openbankingtracker.com/api-aggregators/finicity/vs/plaid), [Fintegration: Plaid vs Finicity 2026 Edition](https://www.fintegrationfs.com/post/plaid-vs-finicity-2026-edition-accuracy-coverage-api-reliability-compared), [SaaS Battle: Plaid vs Finicity 2026](https://trysaasbattle.com/finicity-vs-plaid/)."
