        "q": "Why is UPI's transaction count so much larger than Zelle's?",
        "a": "UPI is a national, interoperable real-time payment rail used for the vast majority of India's digital retail transactions — including small everyday purchases — while Zelle is primarily a peer-to-peer and bill-pay tool layered on top of the US banking system, not a universal checkout rail."
