    "contentMarkdown": "Payment orchestration has become its own infrastructure category, distinct from any single gateway. Here are nine platforms worth knowing, each built for a slightly different use case.\n\n## Enterprise-scale unified commerce\n\n**Adyen** — Best known for unified commerce infrastructure spanning online, in-store, and platform payments in a single stack.\n\n**Checkout.com** — An API-first payments platform built for scalable, developer-controlled integrations.\n\n## Multi-acquirer and marketplace routing\n\n**APEXX Global** — Focused on marketplace and multi-acquirer setups, routing transactions across several processors at once.\n\n**Corefy** — Built around global payment method integration, connecting merchants to a wide spread of local payment options.\n\n## Workflow and gateway flexibility\n\n**Primer** — Centers on automated payment workflow customization, letting teams build and adjust checkout logic without re-engineering integrations.\n\n**Spreedly** — Connects to multiple payment gateways through a single integration, popular with SaaS, travel, and marketplace businesses.\n\n**BlueSnap** — A hybrid gateway-and-orchestration platform combining embedded payments, fraud prevention, and subscription billing.\n\n## Open-source and cloud-native\n\n**Hyperswitch** — An open-source option built for teams that want direct control over transaction routing logic rather than a black-box vendor.\n\n**Gr4vy** — A cloud-native payments infrastructure platform designed for flexible, composable orchestration.\n\n## Regional specialists\n\n**Yuno** and **PayU** round out the list for geography-specific needs — Yuno for businesses expanding into LATAM and APAC with deep localization, and PayU for strong alternative-payment-method coverage across Central/Eastern Europe, LATAM, and Africa.\n\n## How to actually choose\n\nBuyers evaluating this space consistently land on the same lesson: the best platform isn't the one with the longest connector list, but the one matching a specific business's payment flows, regions, compliance needs, and team structure. Enterprise buyers in particular tend to weigh routing depth, token control, and global coverage over marketing claims, since those factors determine how much of a failed-payment problem orchestration actually solves in practice.\n\n## Sources\n\n[Yuno: Top Payment Orchestration Platforms 2026](https://y.uno/post/top-payment-orchestration-platforms-2026), [Solidgate: 8 Best Payment Orchestration Platforms Compared](https://solidgate.com/blog/best-payment-orchestration-platforms/), [Corefy: Top 10 Payment Orchestration Platforms](https://corefy.com/blog/top-payment-orchestration-platforms)."
