    "contentMarkdown": "A refer-a-friend bonus in a fintech app looks simple on the surface — share a link, get paid — but the payout is conditioned on a specific chain of verified actions designed to filter out fraud and reward genuine new customers.\n\n## The qualifying-action structure\n\nReferral programs are typically two-sided: both the person sharing the link and the new signup receive a reward once conditions are met, funded out of the company's customer acquisition spend rather than existing user funds. The trigger for payout is rarely just \"sign up\" — it's usually a chain of steps, commonly account verification followed by a minimum deposit, first transaction, or direct deposit setup within a defined window, such as a set dollar amount within 30 to 45 days. Publicly documented examples illustrate the pattern differently but consistently: some apps pay a bonus once the referred user sends a first payment above a minimum threshold within a short window, while others require a new account plus a direct deposit above a set amount within a longer window before releasing a larger reward. Where a company offers multiple products, reward size frequently scales with which product the referred friend actually adopts, since a mortgage or investment account signup is worth more to the company than a basic checking account.\n\n## How to evaluate a referral offer before sharing it\n\nRead the specific qualifying action, not just the advertised bonus figure — the amount is meaningless without knowing what deposit or activity threshold triggers it and by when. Check whether the reward is paid as cash, in-app credit, or a redeemable balance, since some rewards come with their own withdrawal restrictions. Confirm the program is still active on the company's own app or official site rather than a third-party aggregator, since referral terms and bonus amounts are adjusted often and stale listings are common.\n\n## Sources\n\n[GrowSurf - Fintech Referral Program Examples 2026](https://growsurf.com/examples/fintech-referral-programs/), [Referral Factory - Best Fintech Referral Programs](https://referral-factory.com/learn/best-fintech-referral-programs)."
