    "contentMarkdown": "Checking account bonuses advertised as several hundred to a few thousand dollars aren't handed out for opening an account — they're structured around a specific direct-deposit condition that has to be met within a defined window before the bank pays anything.\n\n## The direct-deposit gating mechanic\n\nThe standard structure requires a new customer to open an account and then receive qualifying direct deposits totaling a set amount within a defined window, commonly 90 days. The bonus size and the required deposit amount scale together: smaller bonuses tend to require smaller cumulative deposits, while the largest advertised bonuses require correspondingly large deposit totals, sometimes across multiple qualifying deposits rather than one lump sum. This is a separate mechanic from ongoing monthly fee waivers, which are usually tied to a lower bar — maintaining a minimum daily or monthly balance, or receiving a smaller recurring deposit — and apply every month rather than once. Once the qualifying condition is met, banks typically pay the bonus within a set number of business days rather than instantly, and many attach a minimum account-tenure requirement afterward, reversing the bonus if the account is closed too soon.\n\n## How to evaluate a bank bonus before opening an account\n\nRead the precise definition of a \"qualifying direct deposit\" — it typically must originate from an employer, payroll provider or government benefits system, and transfers from your own other accounts usually don't count, which is the most common reason people miss out on an advertised bonus. Check the exact deposit total and time window required, and confirm the account-tenure requirement to keep the bonus after it posts. Finally, remember bank bonuses are generally treated as taxable income and can trigger a 1099 form above a certain threshold, so factor that into the real value received.\n\n## Sources\n\n[Bankrate - Best Bank Bonuses July 2026](https://www.bankrate.com/banking/best-bank-account-bonuses-and-promotions/), [NerdWallet - Best Bank Bonuses 2026](https://www.nerdwallet.com/banking/best/bank-bonuses-and-promotions)."
