    "contentMarkdown": "A decade after launch, UPI isn't just India's dominant payment rail — it's the world's largest real-time payments system, period.\n\n## The numbers\n\n- **23.2 billion transactions** worth ₹29.9 trillion processed through UPI in May 2026 alone — a new monthly high.\n- **₹314 lakh crore** — total UPI value moved in FY2025-26, across 24,162 crore transactions, up 30% year-on-year in volume.\n- **85%** — UPI's share of India's digital retail payments in FY26, up from 81% the year before.\n- **839 million** active UPI users, roughly 24% of India's entire population.\n- **49%** — India's share of global real-time payment transaction volume, more than three times Brazil's Pix (14%).\n- **691 banks** are now live on UPI, up from just 216 banks in 2021 — more than tripling the network in under five years.\n\n## Why it matters\n\nUPI's growth curve keeps defying \"it must be plateauing by now\" predictions — daily transactions now average over 737 million. For anyone building payments products in or for India, UPI isn't a channel to support, it's the default rail everything else gets compared against, and the network effect of more banks, more merchants, and more users keeps compounding a full decade in. Cards, wallets, and cash are now the exception in Indian retail, not the norm.\n\n## Sources\n\n[UPI Hits New High in May 2026, ANI News](https://www.aninews.in/news/business/upi-hits-new-high-in-may-2026-with-232-billion-transactions-worth-rs-299-trillion-npci-data-shows20260602155337/), [India's UPI Becomes World's Largest Digital Payment System, The Researchers](https://www.theresearchers.us/2026/05/01/upi-world-largest-payments-india/)."
